A freak accident
has left one person dead and fourteen others injured. According
to ER24, the multiple-vehicle collision took place on Monday (23 July)on the
President Fouche and Malibongwe Road intersection in Randburg, Joburg. Paramedics allegedly
arrived on the scene and found a taxi lying on its roof on the side of the
road. Six other
vehicles were reportedly also involved in the accident. When
paramedics attended to the scene, they found two people lying in the front of
the taxi. One of the
passengers, a male, was found with multiple injuries with no visible signs of
life. He was
declared dead on the scene. The other
passenger was in a serious condition and was rushed to hospital. Thirteen
other patients sustained minor and moderate injuries and were rushed to nearby
hospitals for treatment, ER24 said.